{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"isogonal-wedded-catfish","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nAdd a 7th link relation `caused_by` (directional, non-blocking, non-cycle-inducing, Jira-unmapped) expressing \"this bug was caused by that ticket/change\", making bug provenance a first-class graph edge so \"source of bugs\" is a real traversal.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/schemas/common.schema.json` — add `caused_by` to the `relation` enum (canonical source).\n- `src/rebar/types.py` — regenerate the `Relation` Literal via `python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types`.\n- `src/rebar/graph/_links.py` — add `caused_by` to `CANONICAL_RELATIONS`; non-blocking, non-cycle like `discovered_from`.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/help/link.txt`, `src/rebar/_mcp_writes.py`, `docs/ticket-model.md`, `docs/event-schema.md`, `docs/cli-reference.md` — document it.\n- `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_links.py` — leave `caused_by` intentionally Jira-unmapped (like `discovered_from`).\n- `tests/unit/graph/test_caused_by_relation.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nFollow the `discovered_from` precedent exactly (directional, non-blocking, non-cycle, Jira-unmapped) so the change is purely additive: old LINK events and the reducer stay valid, no persisted data is rewritten, and back-out is simply ceasing to emit the value. A dedicated relation (not reusing `discovered_from`, whose semantics are temporal not causal) is required so recovery-time and source-of-bugs can traverse causation directly.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (real temp store): `link a b caused_by` round-trips and appears in reduced links with relation `caused_by`; a `caused_by` self-cycle does not raise; an old LINK event without the relation still reduces.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/graph/test_caused_by_relation.py` passes: `rebar link <a> <b> caused_by` exits 0 and `rebar show <a> --output json | jq -e '.links[]|select(.relation==\"caused_by\")'` matches.\n- [ ] the generated `Relation` literal in `src/rebar/types.py` includes `caused_by` and the schema enum has 7 values — unit test asserts membership.\n- [ ] a pre-existing LINK event with a legacy relation still reduces without error (back-compat) — unit test asserts unchanged reducer output for a fixture of old links.","id":"0b96-cbcb-0ea2-479d","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","schema"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Add caused_by as a 7th link relation (additive, discovered_from precedent)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416765389784001,"uuid":"d64755ce-843a-4ac1-b985-7822dcbf784c"}